The paper proposes a new approach for metric pose retrieval in autonomous systems, which involves using boosted classifiers to classify landmark observations and directly obtain correspondences as classifier scores. This approach is evaluated through experiments, demonstrating its superiority over state-of-the-art descriptor matching methods. Given the focus on computer vision and robotics, as well as the use of machine learning techniques, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are computer vision (cs.CV), robotics (cs.RO), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and multimedia (cs.MM).
